headline: EOG Resources set to boost shareholder returns
summary: EOG Resources said on Friday its debt levels in the near term would put the oil and gas producer in a position to allocate more than 100% of free-cash-flow for shareholder returns.  Shares of the company rose 4.8% to $132.54 in afternoon trade.  The company said it would raise its debt balance to a range of $5 to $6 billion in the next 12 to 18 months, which would make additional cash available for investor payouts.
